line.comment: * SCRIPT NAME: plugin.zanzal.PwnMi.attack
* DESCRIPTION: Confirm and execute the selected attack
* and process the results.
* AUTHOR: Zanzal DATE: 16 December 2013
* NOTES: All labled sub routines are exit procedures that involve
* cleanup and/or application of results. This command uses voice
* feedback to add to immersion, but the menu code and voice code
* also tends to make it look messy.
* LICENSE: CC-BY-SA 4.0 International - http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/legalcode
* We want to give the user an idea of what might happen if this command is executed.
* So analyze the values given and determine what is the highest risk and the highest
* priviledge increase.
* common menu code
* plugin settings
* Create the attack confirmation menu. This will display a risk assessment for the attack.
* One option - Go back
* Failure index just points to the suspicion loss minimum entry so we know how much
* suspicion to assign in the event of dialog failure.
* Social Command - put them in the pilot seat so they can talk
* Check for instant failure if they don't like you.
* random chance of immediate failure
* If the command has a cost we need to prompt to confirm
* If player backs out that he gets ratted out and the command gets used up
* $victims is either an empty array which means the $target is the victim of the
* attack or else it describes a selection criteria using $target as the origin.
* random stations within a hop range of 1 from $target
* include $target
* add other stations in range
* Make sure we can't accidently reference this list
* Select stations within a hop range of 1 from $target
* include $target
* add other stations in range
* Remote Port Scan only allows targets that have not been port scanned.
* Make sure we can't accidently reference this list
* Attack Approval Received - No backing out
* By this point we should have already taken care of the following:
* 1. Confirmed the users permission to proceed
* 2. Selected a random NPC to use for some social engineering attacks.
* 3. Confirmed and deducted any money costs associated with using the command.
* 4. Determined target and who the victims will be. Now we just need to process and calculate the results.
* The following code now is responsible for executing the attack:
* actual cost was made negative
* create fake id
* Remote Port Scan disables Port Scan on Target
* These command use the fake id
* Disable the command so it cannot be used again on this station.

sval.val: Pwny Express
invalid $victims
